== 典礼资讯 ==
[[File:Steve_Martin_2011.jpg|130px]]担任第75届奥斯卡颁奖典礼主持人。]]
2002年11月，美国电影艺术与科学学院聘请了老牌奥斯卡电视转播制作人吉尔·凯茨负责本届晚会的制作，这也是他第11次担任奥斯卡颁奖典礼的制作人<ref>{{cite news | last = Archerd | first = Army | title = Cates to Lead Oscarcast | work = Variety | publisher = PMC | page = 2 | date = 2002-11-04}}</ref>。学院主席弗兰克·皮尔森对此在一次新闻发布会上表示，之前已10次接掌的凯茨在经验上无人能及。“吉尔几乎为颁奖晚会发明出了一种风格流派。我们对能够邀请他来呈现奥斯卡金像奖75周年的这场特别晚会感到非常荣幸”<ref>{{cite news | title = Gil Cates to Produce 75th Anniversary Oscar® Telecast | url = http://www.oscars.org/press/pressreleases/2002/02.11.04.html | accessdate = 2008-07-18 | newspaper = Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences | date = 2004-11-04 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080718131254/http://www.oscars.org/press/pressreleases/2002/02.11.04.html | archivedate = 2008-07-18}}</ref>。几天后，喜剧演员[[史提夫·马丁|史提夫·马丁]]获选成为颁奖典礼的[[主持人|主持人]]。对此凯茨表示：他之所以选择再度邀请这位喜剧老将主持是因为他“机智、聪明、敏锐、风趣，总是能够把握主动权。等等，我还忘了点什么。对了，（他还能）让人笑得前俯后仰”<ref>{{cite news | title = Steve Martin to host 75th Oscars | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413140727/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/2417951.stm | archivedate = 2014-04-13 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/2417951.stm | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = BBC News | publisher = BBC | date = 2002-11-07}}</ref>。《[[洛杉矶时报|洛杉矶时报]]》刊文称，凯茨曾就担任主持人事宜联系另一位喜剧演员[[比利·克里斯托|比利·克里斯托]]，但由于后者一直没有下定决心，所以凯茨再联系了马丁<ref>{{cite news | last = Welkos | first = Robert W. | title = It's Martin for Oscars 2003 | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2002/nov/08/entertainment/et-welkos8 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413132748/http://articles.latimes.com/2002/nov/08/entertainment/et-welkos8 | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Los Angeles Times | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2002-11-08 | archivedate = 2014-04-13 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。马丁在一份声明中表示自己对此深感荣幸，他开玩笑称：“我很高兴能再次主持奥斯卡颁奖典礼，因为担惊受惊和恶心总是能让我减肥”<ref>{{cite news | last = Errico | first = Marcus | title = Martin Meets Oscar Again | url = http://www.eonline.com/news/44147/martin-meets-oscar-again | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = E! | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413142057/http://www.eonline.com/news/44147/martin-meets-oscar-again | publisher = NBCUniversal | date = 2002-11-07 | archivedate = 2014-04-13 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。此外，本次颁奖典礼还是首次通过[[高清晰度电视|高清]]制式进行转播<ref>{{cite news | last = Taub | first = Eric | title = Technology: HDTV's Acceptance Picks Up Pace As Prices Drop and Networks Sign On | archivedate = 2014-04-17 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140417103319/http://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/31/business/technology-hdtv-s-acceptance-picks-up-pace-as-prices-drop-and-networks-sign-on.html | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/31/business/technology-hdtv-s-acceptance-picks-up-pace-as-prices-drop-and-networks-sign-on.html | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = The New York Times | publisher = The New York Times Company | date = 2003-03-31}}</ref>。

为了纪念奥斯卡金像奖75周年，晚会上一个名为奥斯卡大家庭相册的环节中有59位曾获过奖的演员一起出现在舞台上<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|347}}。报幕员内尔·罗斯（{{lang|en|Neil Ross}}）和兰迪·托马斯（{{lang|en|Randy Thomas}}）会报出各位演员的姓名及其获奖的电影片名。到片段末尾时，本届晚会上的获奖演员阿德里安·布罗迪、妮可·基德曼、克里斯·库柏、凯瑟琳·泽塔-琼斯以及[[奥斯卡荣誉奖|奥斯卡荣誉奖]]得主[[彼得·奥图尔|彼得·奥图尔]]都将加入他们的行列<ref>{{cite news | last = Flaningan | first = Kathy | title = Glitz prevails | work = Milwaukee Journal Sentinel | publisher = Journal Communications | date = 2003-03-24 | page = 1E}}</ref>。

此外，[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克战争]]对这次电视转播及周边事项产生了影响。战争爆发的消息传开后，包括[[凯特·布兰切特|凯特·布兰切特]]、[[金·凯瑞|金·凯瑞]]和[[威尔·史密斯|威尔·史密斯]]在内的多位演员谢绝了担任颁奖嘉宾的邀请，理由中既有对安全方面的顾虑，也有出于对军人家属的尊重<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|331}}。[[美国广播公司|美国广播公司]]请求将晚会推迟一星期，但学院主席皮尔森和晚会制作人凯茨没有接受，理由是[[杜比剧院|杜比剧院]]到时还会有别的安排<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|328}}<ref>{{cite news | last = Welkos | first = Robert W. | title = Oscar Gets Ready for a Difficult Role on Wartime Stage | archivedate = 2014-07-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140705055637/http://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/23/news/war-oscars23 | deadurl = no | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/23/news/war-oscars23 | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Los Angeles Times | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2003-03-23 | last2 = Horn | first2 = John}}</ref>。皮尔森还表示，将典礼改期会提高成本，对学院来说过于昂贵<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|329}}。不过他们也宣布晚会前的红地毯活动将会大幅缩减<ref>{{cite news | last = Horn | first = John | last2 = Piccalo | first2 = Gina | last3 = Quintanilla | first3 = Michael | title = Oscar's Red Carpet Fades to Black; Next Question, Will Show Go On? | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/19/news/war-oscars19 | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Los Angeles Times | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2003-03-19 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413132449/http://articles.latimes.com/2003/mar/19/news/war-oscars19 | archivedate = 2014-04-13}}</ref>。沿[[好莱坞大道|好莱坞大道]]两边的看台座位将会拆除，所有购买了这些座位票的观众可以改期到[[第76届奥斯卡金像奖|下一年的颁奖典礼]]时使用<ref>{{cite news | last = Paul | first = Max | title = Not only actors work hard to get to Oscars | work = NBC News | publisher = NBCUniversal | date = 2004-02-28 | archivedate = 2014-04-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413124034/http://www.today.com/id/4398468/ns/today-today_entertainment/t/not-only-actors-work-hard-get-oscars/#.U7eVUlMwnb1 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | url = http://www.today.com/id/4398468/ns/today-today_entertainment/t/not-only-actors-work-hard-get-oscars/#.U0ZQclfn_To}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | last = Oakes | first = Keilly | title = Hollywood Gears Up for Oscar Party | archivedate = 2008-11-22 | url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3495186.stm | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = BBC News | publisher = BBC | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081122153143/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/3495186.stm | deadurl = no | date = 2004-02-28}}</ref>。晚会电视转播的插播广告时间里，[[ABC新闻|ABC新闻]]主播兼[[记者|记者]][[彼得·詹宁斯|彼得·詹宁斯]]将对伊拉克战争的最新进展作简报<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|344}}。

=== 提名电影票房表现 ===
截止2月11日提名名单公布时，五部获最佳影片提名电影在[[美国电影|美国]]的总计[[票房|票房]]收入为4亿8679万9261[[美元|美元]]，平均每部9735万9852美元<ref name="BoxOfficeOscars">{{cite news | title = 2002 Academy Award Nominations and Winner for Best Picture | url = http://boxofficemojo.com/oscar/chart/?yr=2002&p=.htm | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Box Office Mojo | publisher = Amazon.com | archivedate = 2014-07-03 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140703034724/http://boxofficemojo.com/oscar/chart/?yr=2002&p=.htm | deadurl = no}}</ref>。其中《指环王：双塔奇兵》以3亿2108万6387美元位居榜首，之后分别是收入7010万8275美元的《纽约黑帮》，进账6456万8153美元的《芝加哥》，收入2188万3139美元的《时时刻刻》和进账915万3307美元的《钢琴家》<ref name="BoxOfficeOscars" />。

在2002年美国电影票房50强中，有14部电影获得了共计47项提名。其中《指环王：双塔奇兵》（[[亚军|亚军]]）、《我盛大的希腊婚礼》（第5位）、《冰河世纪》（第9位）、《猫鼠游戏》（第11位）、《星际宝贝》（第13位》、《毁灭之路》（第23位）、《小马王》（第35位）、《纽约黑帮》（第37位）和《芝加哥》（第41位）9部获得了最佳影片、动画长片、导演，或表演、编剧类奖项提名<ref name="boxofficemojooscars">{{cite web | archivedate = 2014-04-07 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140407074217/http://boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?asof=2003-02-11&view=releasedate&view2=domestic&yr=2002&sort=gross&order=DESC&p=.htm | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | url = http://boxofficemojo.com/yearly/chart/?asof=2003-02-11&view=releasedate&view2=domestic&yr=2002&sort=gross&order=DESC&p=.htm | title = 2002 Domestic Grosses | publisher = Amazon.com | work = Box Office Mojo}}</ref>。另外5部获提名的分别是《蜘蛛侠》（[[冠军|冠军]]）、《星球大战前传2：克隆人的进攻》（季军）、《少数派报告》（第16位）、《8英里》（第22位）和《时间机器》（第44位）<ref name="boxofficemojooscars" />。

=== 纪录片奖获奖致辞 ===
《科伦拜校园事件》拿下纪录片片奖后不久，导演[[迈克尔·摩尔|迈克尔·摩尔]]公开发言表示反对[[美国总统|美国总统]][[乔治·沃克·布什|乔治·沃克·布什]]和伊拉克战争，称“我们生活在一个以虚假选举选出虚假总统的时代。我们生活在一个人以虚假理由让我们去打战的时代”<ref name="Pond" />{{rp|345}}。剧院内的其他人对此反应不一，有些鼓掌、有些起立致敬、还有些发出嘘声<ref>{{cite news | last = Effron | first = Eric | title = The World: Acting Out; At the Oscars, a Cause and Effect | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140417104416/http://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/30/weekinreview/the-world-acting-out-at-the-oscars-a-cause-and-effect.html | archivedate = 2014-04-17 | deadurl = no | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/30/weekinreview/the-world-acting-out-at-the-oscars-a-cause-and-effect.html | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = The New York Times | publisher = The New York Times Company | date = 2003-03-30}}</ref>。摩尔讲出这番话后不久，主持人马丁开玩笑说：“[[国际卡车司机兄弟会|卡车司机]]正在帮迈克尔·摩尔躲到自己豪华轿车的后车厢里去”<ref>{{cite news | last = Jicha | first = Tom | title = A Night Rules By Decorum. Mostly | archivedate = 2014-04-13 | url = http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2003-03-24/lifestyle/0303240203_1_oscar-night-jennifer-lopez-michael-moore | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Sun-Sentinel | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2003-03-24 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413125433/http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2003-03-24/lifestyle/0303240203_1_oscar-night-jennifer-lopez-michael-moore}}</ref>。

=== 专业评价 ===
本届晚会收到的媒体评价褒贬不一，部分媒体较为正面。《[[今日美国|今日美国]]》电视评论员罗伯特·比安科（{{lang|en|Robert Bianco}}）称赞了马丁的主持表现：“观众们很幸运，马丁拥有两种对于一个好的奥斯卡颁奖典礼主持人来说不可或缺的素质：机智和内涵。这两项都成为他和我们的优势，先赢得观众的信任，然后兴高采烈地嘲笑他们一整晚。”他还指出，颁奖嘉宾和获奖者所提及的政治内容让这样一个通常会很沉闷的夜晚也拥有了一些张力<ref>{{cite news | last = Bianco | first = Robert | title = A jolly good show — for a host of reasons | work = USA Today | publisher = Gannett Company | date = 2003-03-24 | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/2003-03-24-oscar-tv_x.htm | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140407085846/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/movies/movieawards/oscars/2003-03-24-oscar-tv_x.htm | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | archivedate = 2014-04-07}}</ref>。《[[匹兹堡邮报|匹兹堡邮报]]》（{{lang|en|''Pittsburgh Post-Gazette''}}）电视专栏作家罗布·欧文（{{lang|en|Rob Owen}}）对马丁赞不绝口，称他拥有许多颁奖晚会主持人缺少的高雅和机智，无论是对有关自己重返奥斯卡颁奖舞台的反响，还是据称遭到缩小的颁奖典礼规模，马丁都一如既往地以富娱乐性的手法来应对。他还觉得这次对奥斯卡奖历史的纪念内容看起来多了一分紧实，少了一点繁琐<ref>{{cite news | last = Owen | first = Rob | title = Review: Host Martin makes Oscars a great escape from grim reality | url = http://old.post-gazette.com/ae/20030324owen0324p2.asp | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Pittsburgh Post-Gazette | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140407081140/http://old.post-gazette.com/ae/20030324owen0324p2.asp | deadurl = no | publisher = Crain Communications | archivedate = 2014-04-07}}</ref>。《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》的[[汤姆·谢尔斯|汤姆·谢尔斯]]（{{lang|en|Tom Shales}}）也对马丁给予高度评价，称他在把这次晚会提升成一场好节目上有着不可估量的贡献，他还认为节目的气氛虽有些沉闷，但颁奖嘉宾和获奖者的致辞和致敬段落造就了许多难忘的瞬间，而这些瞬间正是这个动荡时期所迫切需要的<ref>{{cite news | last = Shales | first = Tom | title = This Year, The Drama Goes to Oscar | work = The Washington Post | publisher = The Washington Post Company | date = 2003-03-24}}</ref>。

一些媒体出版物对节目的评价较为负面。《[[娱乐周刊|娱乐周刊]]》电视评论员[[肯·塔克|肯·塔克]]（{{lang|en|Ken Tucker}}）感叹，[[第73届奥斯卡金像奖|两年前]]表现精彩、机智的史提夫·马丁这次看起来已经认输并退居二线，把调动全场欢乐气氛的责任让给了喜剧编剧[[布鲁斯·韦兰奇|布鲁斯·韦兰奇]]（{{lang|en|Bruce Vilanch}}），最后得出的只是一批愚笨无聊的台词<ref>{{cite news|last=Tucker |first=Ken |title=The Show |url=http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,440442,00.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070619120647/http://www.ew.com/ew/article/0%2C%2C440442%2C00.html |accessdate=2014-07-05 |work=Entertainment Weekly |publisher=Time Warner |date=2014-04-04 |archivedate=2007-06-19 |deadurl=no }}</ref>。《[[芝加哥论坛报|芝加哥论坛报]]》专栏作家史蒂夫·约翰逊（{{lang|en|Steve Johnson}}）则认为，第二次主持好莱坞最盛大夜晚的马丁看起来——特别是一开始的时候——却有些不在状态，他试图保持一幅乐在其中的形象，但看起来却有些不是那么一回事。约翰逊还表示，马丁只有在摩尔领奖致辞后的表现还算值得称道，不过考虑到战争的爆发，大家可能也无法静下心来出席或观看晚会，很多人都想转台去看{{lang|en|[[CNN|CNN]]}}，马丁的工作也就变成了一件不可能的任务<ref>{{cite news | last = Johnson | first = Steve | title = Telecast stumbles trying to find footing during wartime | url = http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2003-03-24/features/0303240116_1_michael-moore-telecast-steve-martin | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140407093109/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2003-03-24/features/0303240116_1_michael-moore-telecast-steve-martin | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Chicago Tribune | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2003-03-24 | archivedate = 2014-04-07 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。大卫·祖拉维克（{{lang|en|David Zurawik}}）在《[[巴尔的摩太阳报|巴尔的摩太阳报]]》上调侃道：“正当世界上其他地方看到被俘虏的美国军人或是他们尸体的同时，我们却在看主持人史蒂夫·马丁和整整一个剧院的名流一起庆祝他们自以为很重要的事。”他还批评节目中的许多言论和笑话似乎对这场战争视而不见，缺乏足够的尊重<ref>{{cite news | last = Zurawik | first = David | title = A Muted Celebration | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140407085715/http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2003-03-24/features/0303240200_1_sadness-war-in-iraq-telecast | url = http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2003-03-24/features/0303240200_1_sadness-war-in-iraq-telecast | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = The Baltimore Sun | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2003-03-24 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-04-07}}</ref>。

=== 收视率和奖项 ===
本届颁奖典礼通过美国广播公司在美国直播，其播出时段里平均有3304万观众收看，与[[第74届奥斯卡金像奖|前一年]]相比降低了21%<ref>{{cite news | title = War coverage steals some of Academy Awards' thunder | date = 2003-03-25 | url = http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2003-03-25-oscar-ratings_x.htm | work = USA Today | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20121019160511/http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/life/television/news/2003-03-25-oscar-ratings_x.htm | publisher = Gannett Company | first = Gary | last = Levin | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | archivedate = 2012-10-19 | deadurl = no}}</ref>，而所有曾观看部分时段节目的观众总数则估计有6255万<ref>{{cite news | last = Ryan | first = Joal | title = Ratings Bomb as War Rages | url = http://www.eonline.com/news/44851/ratings-bomb-as-war-rages | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = E! | publisher = NBCUniversal | date = 2003-03-25 | archivedate = 2014-04-07 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140407084310/http://www.eonline.com/news/44851/ratings-bomb-as-war-rages}}</ref>。从尼尔森收视率调查的数据看，节目的表现也不及前一年，只吸引了20.58%的家庭观看，收视率为40.34%<ref name="TVB Oscars">{{cite news|title=Academy Awards ratings |work=Television Bureau of Advertising |format=PDF |archivedate=2013-10-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016061652/http://www.tvb.org/media/file/Academy_Awards.pdf |accessdate=2014-05-16 |url=http://www.tvb.org/media/file/Academy_Awards.pdf |deadurl=yes }}</ref>。此外节目在18至49岁年龄段观众群的收视成绩为12.55/35.37，这意味着全美所有18至49岁年龄段人群里有12.55%观看了颁奖典礼，而当时有看电视的该年龄段观众群中则有35.37%选择收看这个节目<ref name="TVB Oscars" />。许多媒体认为，有线新闻电视台对伊拉克战争的报道转移了许多家庭观众的注意，导致节目的收视率大幅下降<ref>{{cite news | last = Johnson | first = Allan | title = Show goes on, but ABC sees its lowest-ever Oscars rating | archivedate = 2014-04-13 | url = http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2003-03-25/news/0303250206_1_oscar-telecast-oscar-cast-picture-award | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413143500/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2003-03-25/news/0303250206_1_oscar-telecast-oscar-cast-picture-award | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Chicago Tribune | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2003-03-25 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。奥斯卡颁奖典礼的收视率从1974年的[[第46届奥斯卡金像奖|第46届颁奖典礼]]开始汇编，而[[尼尔森媒体研究|尼尔森媒体研究]]早在1961年的[[第33届奥斯卡金像奖|第33届颁奖典礼]]就开始记录这一数字，截至2014年的[[第86届奥斯卡金像奖|第86届奥斯卡颁奖典礼]]，无论是按哪个数据计算，第75届颁奖晚会的收视率都是最低的一次<ref>{{cite web | first = Bill | last = Gorman | title = Academy Awards Averages 41.3 Million Viewers; Most Since 2005 | url = http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/03/08/academy-awards-averages-41-3-million-viewers-most-since-2005/44217/ | work = TV by the Numbers | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2010-03-08 | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131101231748/http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2010/03/08/academy-awards-averages-41-3-million-viewers-most-since-2005/44217/ | archivedate = 2013-11-01 | deadurl = yes }}</ref>。

2003年7月，颁奖典礼获得了第55届[[黄金时段艾美奖|黄金时段艾美奖]]的8项提名<ref>{{cite news | archivedate = 2013-06-22 | title = Primetime Emmy Award database | url = http://www.emmys.com/shows/75th-annual-academy-awards | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130622215853/http://www.emmys.com/shows/75th-annual-academy-awards | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Academy of Television Arts and Sciences | publisher = ATAS}}</ref>，并在两个月后赢得了其中三座奖项，分别是最佳综艺或音乐节目类艺术指导奖，最佳综艺、音乐或喜剧节目照明指导奖，以及最佳音乐指导奖<ref>{{cite news | last = Braxton | first = Greg | title = HBO, NBC Are Big Winners in First Wave of Emmys | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140705100646/http://articles.latimes.com/2003/sep/22/entertainment/et-emmylist22 | deadurl = no | url = http://articles.latimes.com/2003/sep/22/entertainment/et-emmylist22 | accessdate = 2014-07-05 | work = Los Angeles Times | publisher = Tribune Company | date = 2002-09-16 | archivedate = 2014-07-05}}</ref>。

== 纪念 ==
奥斯卡颁奖典礼上一年一度的“纪念”致敬环节旨在纪念过去一年中逝世的业内人士，本场晚会上的这一环节由女演员[[苏珊·莎兰登|苏珊·莎兰登]]引出，纪念了以下人士：<ref name="Pond">{{cite book | last = Pond | first = Steve |title=The Big Show: High Times and Dirty Dealings Backstage at the Academy Awards | url = https://archive.org/details/bigshowhightimes00pond | year = 2005 | isbn = 0-571-21193-3 | location = New York, United States |edition= |OCLC= |publisher= Faber and Faber | postscript = .}}</ref>{{rp|346}}
{{col-begin}}
{{col-1-of-2}}
*[[卢·沃瑟曼|卢·沃瑟曼]]（{{lang|en|Lew Wasserman}}）
*[[理查德·赛尔伯特|理查德·赛尔伯特]]（{{lang|en|Richard Sylbert}}）
*[[埃迪·布莱肯|埃迪·布莱肯]]（{{lang|en|Eddie Bracken}}）
*[[乔治·西德尼|乔治·西德尼]]（{{lang|en|George Sidney}}）
*[[凯蒂·胡拉多|凯蒂·胡拉多]]
